article.description: Caity Matter hit four 3-pointers and scored 21 points to lead Ohio State to a 77-35 victory over Northwestern on Sunday.
article.headline: Matter hits four 3s, scores 21 points
article.linkText: What's the Matter? Guard leads Buckeye win
article.story:
EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Caity Matter hit four 3-pointers and
scored 21 points to lead Ohio State (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) to a 77-35 victory over
Northwestern on Sunday.

Michelle Munoz scored 14 points, and LaToya Turner finished with
13 points and seven rebounds for the Buckeyes (10-4, 2-1 Big Ten).

Ifeoma Okonkwo had 10 points and five rebounds for Northwestern
(7-7, 0-3).

Ohio State shot 50 percent from the field, while Northwestern
shot just 30 percent.

Ohio State shot 6-for-11 from 3-point range in the first half
and built a 42-17 lead by the break.

Northwestern shot 2-for-9 from beyond the arc in the first half
and 4-for-17 in the game.

Ohio State scored 31 points off turnovers, while Northwestern
scored just two points off turnovers.
